        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:24PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mill Creek, or 16 miles north of Pulga, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail. Funnel
clouds possible.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pulga, Mill Creek, Stirling City, Storrie, Belden, Lovelock, Butte
Meadows, Tobin, and Concow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
